    lesson: 'The capstone brief answers five things plainly: funding status (which color, current/expired/canceled, where in the lifecycle), legal constraints (purpose/time/amount, CR limits, ADA risk), execution risks (what the variance and obligation rate really show), decisions needed (the ask and whether the requested fund move is legally available), and evidence gaps (what an auditor would demand that the packet lacks). Each conclusion is defended with the actual rule, not the slide.',
